                            <comment id="13056447" author="srowen" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2011 12:10:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 from me, I think this is not only a good change but well executed. It is also something I think needed to get done for 1.0, as it gets rid of deprecations and increases standardization, so a bonus point for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13056805" author="ssc" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2011 22:41:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you very much, Sean. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder whether there is some article/paper that describes this particular approach of implementing Naive Bayes? A colleague of mine with a much deeper statistics background and me took a look at the details of the computation today and we were left with some open questions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13059337" author="ssc" created="Mon, 4 Jul 2011 07:50:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Reworked patch committed. Special thanks goes to Christoph Boden for his help on this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
